title: Bug 109350: Output parameter should display in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from the Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, when viewing the query result page, no data is returned. The actual result should be that the output parameter is displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: When viewing the query result page, no data is returned.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database.
2. Navigate to the query result page.
3. Verify that no data is returned.
4. Open the edit data set dialog and verify that the output parameter is displayed.
